HEADWORD: Nargileh
<hw>Nar"gi*leh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per. <ets>n⟦amac⟧rgh⟦imac⟧l</ets>, prop., a
cocoanut; prob. so called because first made of a cocoanut.]</ety>
<def>An apparatus for smoking tobacco. It has a long flexible tube, and
the smoke is drawn through water. Also called <er>hoookah</er> and
<altname>water pipe</altname>. Functionally similar to the
<er>hubble-bubble</er>, a simplified form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

